<section>
<title>NVIDIA Drivers Update</title>
<body>

<p>
Recently <c>x11-drivers/nvidia-drivers</c> has been updated to include all
available driver versions, including the one found in
<c>x11-drivers/nvidia-legacy-drivers</c>, as posted by <mail
link="cardoe@gentoo.org">Doug Goldstein</mail> on <uri
link="http://blog.cardoe.com/archives/2007/07/19/nvidia-drivers-updates/">
Gentoo Planet</uri>. The nvidia-legacy-drivers package have been removed in 
favor of the 71xx driver version now available in nvidia-drivers. In 
accordance with this change, <mail link="nightmorph@gentoo.org">Josh Saddler
</mail> has updated the 
<uri link="http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/nvidia-guide.xml">NVIDIA guide</uri>.
</p>

<p>
While the NVIDIA drivers ebuild will perform some auto detection to ensure that 
the right driver for your card gets installed, you may still need to mask later
versions to get the one that you need. Josh Saddler has updated the guide with
regards to this change, which can also be found and in NVIDIA's <uri
link="http://www.nvidia.com/object/IO_32667.html">hardware compatibility
list</uri>.
</p>

</body>
</section>

