<section>
<title>forums.gentoo.org</title>

<body>

<p><b>Portato: A Portage GUI</b></p>

<p>
<uri link="http://forums.gentoo.org/profile.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=126014">
Necoro</uri> announced a GTK+ based GUI for Portage:
<uri link="http://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic-t-495971-highlight-.html">Portato
</uri> in the forums (albeit in German). This GUI was designed to help users
when the CLI isn't sufficient. For example, when emerging a package with lots
of dependencies and USE flags. This is made easier to do with a graphical
front-end with the use of an Emerge Queue, which updates automatically and shows
dependencies. Necoro stated that Portato wasn't meant as a replacement for the
CLI tools but is more comfortable in various situations.
</p>

<p>
To get Portato, execute the following commands:
</p>

<pre caption="How to get Portato">
# <i> layman -o http://portato.sf.net/layman.xml -S </i>
# <i> layman -o http://portato.sf.net/layman.xml -a portato </i>
</pre>

</body>
</section>

